Villarreal coach, Javier Calleja while describing Samuel Chukwueze referees him the Super Eagles winger as a complete player. According to his coach, Calleja, the Nigerian is finally showing the work the technical team has put it to develop him while adding he can become a great player if he continues working hard. “We’ve worked a lot and Samu is a very complete player. If he continues on this path, he’ll become a really top footballer,” he said. The 21-year-old has netted three goals while providing four assists for Villarreal in 28 appearances this season. Since the restart of the LaLiga, Chukwueze has been in fine form, contributing two assists out of the three goals scored by his side while helping the team to secure nine maximum points.